description: McKay-Thompson series of class 5B for the Monster group with a(0) = 0.
references: J. H. Conway and S. P. Norton, Monstrous Moonshine, Bull. Lond. Math. Soc. 11 (1979) 308-339.
D. Ford, J. McKay and S. P. Norton, ``More on replicable functions,'' Commun. Algebra 22, No. 13, 5175-5193 (1994).
McKay, John; Strauss, Hubertus. The q-series of monstrous moonshine and the decomposition of the head characters. Comm. Algebra 18 (1990), no. 1, 253-278.
N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
links: Index entries for McKay-Thompson series for Monster simple group
formula: Expansion of 6 + (eta(q) / eta(q^5))^6 in powers of q. - _Michael Somos_, Apr 30 2004a(n) = A045483(n) = A106248(n) unless n=0.
mathematica: a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ 6 + 1/q (QPochhammer[ q] / QPochhammer[ q^5])^6, {q, 0, n}] (* _Michael Somos_, May 22 2013 *)
prog: (PARI) {a(n) = local(A); if( n<-1, 0, n++; A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( 6*x + (eta(x + A) / eta(x^5 + A))^6, n))} /* _Michael Somos_, Apr 30 2004 */(PARI) {a(n) = local(A, k); if( n<-1, 0, k = (sqrtint(40*n + 48) + 7)\10; A = x * (sum(i=-k, k, (-1)^i * x^((5*i^2 + 3*i)/2), x^2 * O(x^n)) / sum(i=-k, k, (-1)^i * x^((5*i^2 + i)/2), x^2 * O(x^n)))^5; polcoeff( 1/A - A - 5, n)) /* _Michael Somos_, Apr 30 2004 */
